31/05/2009
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- Five Serbs sentenced for war crimes in Kosovo have appealed their convictions, The Hague war crimes tribunal (ICTY) said on Friday (May 29th). They are Former Yugoslav National Army (JNA) General Vladimir Lazarevic, former Yugoslav Prime Minister Nikola Sainovic, former JNA commander Nebojsa Pavkovic, former Serbian police chief Sreten Lukic and ex-Yugoslav Defence Minister Dragoljub Ojdanic. In February, the five received sentences of between 15 and 22 years in prison for crimes committed during the 1998-1999 Kosovo conflict. (AFP, Beta, Focus - 29/05/09)
